 behavior as it relates to his or her group. She finds that the value patterns of the religious groups differ significantly from one another, and she is able to highlight those factors that appear to have contributed most toward rescue within each group.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAltruism. 0aMotivation (Psychology). 0aPersonality and culture. 0aReligion and culture. 0aRighteous Gentiles in the HolocaustxAttitudes. 0aRighteous Gentiles in the HolocaustxPsychology. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xJewsxRescue. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030010063140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030013040940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300130409423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300130409/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY